<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>    The Council</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of Ascension Alliance consists of those members who are elected or appointed to serve as officers and leaders of the guild.<br>
<br>
General guidelines:<br>
Each member of the council has an equal vote in all matters of policy and decisions affecting the guild.<br>
<br>
Each player may hold only one position on The Council (one player, one vote).<br>
<br>
When a member is promoted to officer, all of their guilded characters become officers.<br>
<br>
Responsibilities of Guild Officers:<br>
The Guild Officers may schedule meetings, establish agendas, and preside at Guild Meetings and meetings of The Council. In addition, they are the only members of the guild who can invite or remove members. <br>
<br>
Selection of Guild Officers:<br>
The founding officers shall be determined by self-nomination and majority consensus among the founding members. Thereafter, the council shall establish a policy regarding terms of office and method for replacing officers. It is anticipated that an officer shall remain in position as long as said officer is willing and able to perform the duties of office.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>    The Guild Leader</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is a necessity created by the EverQuest requirements for player guilds.<br>
<br>
Responsibilities of the Guild Leader:<br>
The Guild Leader is the only member of the guild who can create the guild, invite officers, transfer guild leadership, or disband the entire guild. In Ascension Alliance, the designated Guild Leader is a member of The Council and has an equal vote on all matters concerning the guild. The designated Guild Leader has no individual authority and is bound to abide by the judgment of The Council on all matters concerning the guild.<br>
<br>
Selection of the Guild Leader:<br>
The founding guild leader shall be determined by self-nomination and majority consensus among the founding members. Thereafter, the council shall establish a policy regarding terms of office and method for replacing the guild leader. It is anticipated that a guild leader shall remain in position as long as said guild leader is willing and able to perform the duties of office.<br>
